Logical schema for temporary file location

Specify the name of logical schema defining the location the temporary file will be stored before uploading to Object Storage. This must be a File technology logical schema. The temporary file will be stored on local file system where ODI agent is running.

SNP_TRT : LKM File to ADWC Copy Direct

COMPONENT NAME: LKM SQL to ADWC Copy Direct COMPONENT VERSION: 1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.2.1.4.0 or above
DESCRIPTION
This LKM will load data from SQL source to Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud using Oracle Object Storage as intermediate staging. The result from SQL query is first loaded into Oracle Object Storage staging area. Then we use dbms_cloud.copy_data() function to load data from Object Storage directly into ADWC target table. All target columns will be loaded, not matter whether they are mapped or not. Only transformations on source are supported. The user must set TEMP_OBJECT_STORAGE_SCHEMA and TEMP_FILE_SCHEMA KM option to designate temporary storage locations. This LKM has to be used as standalone, no IKM is needed.
Note : LKM SQL to ADWC Copy Direct has two different sets of KM options for formatting date/time datatypes. 1. UNLOAD_DATE_FORMAT/UNLOAD_TIMESTAMP_FORMAT are used while unloading SQL query into text file. The formatting syntax is conform to Java Date and Time Patterns. 2. DATE_FORMAT is used while loading object storage text file into ADWC. The formatting syntax is conform to Oracle database syntax for formatting DATE datatype. If you are loading into TIMESTAMP column use Advanced option ADD_FORMAT_PROPERTIES to add timestampformat property.
It is very important to synchronize UNLOAD_DATE_FORMAT/UNLOAD_TIMESTAMP_FORMAT and DATE_FORMAT/timestampformat to use compatible format settings, even though they are using different syntax.
Here is an example of loading from source TIMESTAMP column into target TIMESTAMP column.
UNLOAD_TIMESTAMP_FORMAT = yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS ADD_FORMAT_PROPERTIES = 'timestampformat' VALUE 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS.FF3'
Also make sure that TIMESTAMP column precision allows for the given format to be stored.
